<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eritrea to Get COMESA's Road Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Eritrea is to obtain yellow
card and road transport facilitation within the Common Market for
Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA).
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the latest issue of weekly
''Eritrea Profile'', a COMESA seminar on the yellow card scheme
operations and road transport facilitation was held recently in
Asmara, capital of Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was designed to familiarize the private sector,
business community and government institutions in Eritrea with
the various COMESA transport facilitation instruments that will
enable them to explore the business opportunities available in
the COMESA region.
</P>
<P>
In an opening statement, Bunyabarenzi (one name), director of
transport and communications in the COMESA secretariat, called on
the entire business community in Eritrea to play a more effective
role in using the various COMESA transport facilitation
instruments and benefit from the advantages of the vast market
opportunities available in the COMESA region.
</P>
<P>
He said the immediate tasks of the regional grouping are to
remove all barriers to intra-COMESA trade and investment and
increase competitiveness in all areas, including production and
service sectors.
</P>
<P>
The COMESA treaty came into force on December 8, 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
