<HEADLINE> Romania Regards Hungary as Strategic Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Prime Minister Victor
Ciorbea said that Hungary and Romania are strategic partners, the
Hungarian newspaper People's Liberty reported today.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark in an interview with Hungarian reporters two
days before leaving for Hungary, the first country he will visit
after he became the head of government in November 1996.
</P>
<P>
Romania and Hungary should further strengthen their economic
and military ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the strategic importance of this partnership lies
in the strategic positions of and frequent armed conflicts in the
region where the two countries belong. 
