<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Power Station to Be Completed in Laos by 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 10 (Xinhua) -- A 60-Megawatt hydro-power station
will be completed in Laos by 1999 to help eliminate poverty in the
country, the country's official news agency KPL reported today.
</P>
<P>
The diversion dam is reported to be 80 kilometers north of the
capital Vientiane.
</P>
<P>
KPL said the project, expected to be operational by the end of
1999, will provide electricity to nearby households and industries.
</P>
<P>
Laos will also sell some of the energy to Thailand, which is
expected to earn some 10 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The cost of the project, including a 140-kilometer transmission
line, is estimated at 112.6 million dollars, KPL added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
