<HEADLINE> Georgia Says It Should Own Part of Black Sea Fleet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Georgian President Eduard
Shevardnadze said today that the division of the Black Sea Fleet
was not fair and that Georgia should claim part of the fleet's
warships.
</P>
<P>
Shevardnadze made the remarks in a regular speech to Georgian
citizens. He said that Russia withdrew all the fleet from Georgia
without any consultations with Georgian leaders.
</P>
<P>
Russia took an "obviously unfair" attitude toward Georgia over
the division of the Black Sea fleet, although the two countries
have established a strategic partnership, the Georgian president
said.
</P>
<P>
No comment from Russian officials was reported so far. 
</P>
