<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Takes up Top WHO Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean medical scientist Mike
Mbizvo has been appointed to head a task force researching on
reproductive health in the Wold Health Organization, the most
senior post the world body has ever awarded to an African.
</P>
<P>
Mbizvo (45), who assumes duty in general on May 1 this year,
competed with 20 other top scientists in the world who had also
been nominated for the post, the Zimbabwe News Agency Ziana
reported today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Ziana, Mbizvo said this will be the first
time the WHO has appointed an African medical scientist to head a
research team.
</P>
<P>
Mbizvo, also an associate research professor at University of
Zimbabwe, has been internationally acclaimed for his research of
male infertility, epidemiology of the Human Immuno-Deficiency
Virus which causes AIDS and risks mortality of women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
