<HEADLINE> EU Expresses Great Concern on Situation in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 10 (Xinhua) -- The European Union said today in
a declaration that it was deeply concerned with the situation in
Albania and its possible implications for the region.
</P>
<P>
The EU called for "maximum self-restraint" from all sides and
urged that further violence be avoided.
</P>
<P>
It also called upon the Albanian authorities and all other
parties to respect human rights, including minority rights, and
fundamental freedom consistent with Albania's international
obligations.
</P>
<P>
"The EU calls upon Albanian political forces to engage in
dialogue, to work together in a responsible manner to solve the
present crisis as soon as possible and to establish a government
which enjoys broad support," the declaration stated.
</P>
<P>
The EU said it welcomed the decision of the chairman-in-office
of the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE)
to send a personal representative to Albania and urged Albania, as
a member of the OSCE, to fully cooperate with his mission.
</P>
<P>
It also urged the Albanian government to work with the
International Monetary Fund/World Bank mission to reach agreement
on ways of ending the present crisis, controlling the investment
schemes and restoring economic well-being on the basis of an
agreed IMF-program. 
</P>
