<HEADLINE> 19,000 UNITA fighters Leave Assembly Camps in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 10 (Xinhua) -- More than 19,000 fighters from
opposition National Union for the Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA) have left Angola's assembly camps so far.
</P>
<P>
Out of the registered UNITA 65,964 fighters in the 15 assembly
camps throughout Angola, only 31,536 remain there, according to
data issued by the U.N. Verification Team here today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the pace of reorganizing UNITA military forces is
also very slow as by now only about 6,900 out of the nearly
18,600 UNITA ex-soldiers chosen have joined the army of national
unity.
</P>
<P>
The quota for UNITA fighters to join the unified army is
26,300 under the Lusaka peace accord signed in November, 1994.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,500 out of 4,905 UNITA policemen have left the
assembly camps, showed the data.
</P>
<P>
UNITA has dismobilized 2,028 child soldiers under age 18 since
September 1996. 
