<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Farmers Advised to Sow Anti-Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian farmers were today
advised to sow anti-drought, short-maturing crops as well as
cultivate plain areas.
</P>
<P>
The National Meteorological Services Agency of Ethiopia
forecast that dry weather, prevalent for a long time in most
parts of the country, will not change in the coming 10 days.
</P>
<P>
Despite expectations of good rainfall distribution this month,
the amount of rainfall in some parts of the country would be
minimal, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
The agency warned that this year cultivation would be hampered
in regions where expected rainfall is small.
</P>
<P>
The season with short rains, usually starting from
mid-February to May in Ethiopia, has not come until March this
year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the agency said that no change is expected in the
southern and southern-eastern lowland areas where there is acute
water shortage for people and animals due to failure of rains
since last September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
