Uganda, including the rehabilitation of the Aga Khan School
complex in Kampala.
</P>
<P>
Aga Khan, 60, who arrived here on Sunday for an eight-day
visit to the east African region, has several million followers
in 25 countries in Asia, Africa, Mid-East, Europe and North
America and founded the group of the network in 1960. He is the
network's principal shareholder. 
