<HEADLINE> Palestinians Clash With Israeli Soldiers In Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Amid mounting tensions between
the Israelis and the Palestinians, the Israeli military
authorities today declared Hebron a "closed military zone"
following clashes between Palestinian youths and Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
According to a report of JMCC, a Palestinian press service based
in East Jerusalem, the clashes took place after the arrival of Israeli
bulldozers, accompanied by some 100 soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The bulldozers began work on a new road between the settlement
of Kiryat Arba and the Ibrahimi Mosque in the center of the West
Bank city, running over Palestinian land adjacent to the Jewish
settlement. The land was planted with grape vines and olive trees.
</P>
<P>
Some Palestinian protesters suffered minor injuries during
clashes with Israeli soldiers, border guards and police.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some 200 Palestinian protesters marched from Beit
Sahur, near Bethlehem, toward Har Homa, site of the would-be
new Jewish settlement in the Arab East Jerusalem, only to be
stopped by Israeli security forces at the Jerusalem municipal
boundaries.
</P>
<P>
In East Jerusalem itself, the PLO Office Orient House
became a scene of confrontation between Palestinian residents and
Israeli rightwingers this afternoon. Israeli and Palestinian
demonstrators shouted insults to each other across the street
and briefly scuffled until they were separated by police.
</P>
<P>
While Faisal Husseini, member of the Executive Committee of the
Palestine Liberation Organization, was meeting with three members
of the Israeli Knesset (parliament) Interior Committee, another
member of the committee, Benny Elon, joined the rightwing
demonstrators calling on the government to close Orient
House. Elon is from the ultra-right party of Moledet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
