<HEADLINE> Zambia to Launch Road Investment Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Zambia announced here today it
will launch a road investment program worth 820 million U.S.
Dollars by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Acting Communications and Transport Minister Kelly Walubita
said the two-phase 10-year program will be funded by the
country's donor community and Zambia's road charge collections.
</P>
<P>
The program is aimed at the systematical rehabilitation of a
core road network so as to allow the maintenance of these roads
to be carried out on a regular basis.
</P>
<P>
The program will also help improve access to remote areas,
said the acting minister.
</P>
<P>
Walubita said the program will check the backlog maintenance,
assuring that a good proportion of the road network will be
restored. 
</P>
