<HEADLINE> French FM Meets Chinese Army General Staff Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 10 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Herve de
Charette said today during a meeting with General Fu Quanyou,
chief of the General Staff of the People's Liberation Army of
China, that the French government highly estimates the foreign
policy of the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
He said that France and China hold identical views over many
international issues and are having cooperation and dialogue in
some important fields.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Franco-Chinese relations make up an important
part of France's foreign policy, and that the visits to France of
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Chinese Premier Li Peng in 1994
and 1996 have greatly pushed forward Franco-Chinese cooperation.
</P>
<P>
De Charette also said that the visit to be paid by French
President Jacques Chirac to China in May will be an important step
in developing Franco-Chinese relations.
</P>
<P>
He said that France and China share a joint desire to develop
bilateral relations in the political, economic, trade and military
fields, and that the two countries have increased high level
dialogue on political issues and security since 1996.
</P>
<P>
Fu Quanyou said that the Chinese government and army pay great
importance to developing relations with the French government and
the French army.
</P>
<P>
He said that over the past two years, Sino-French relations
have further developed and high-level contacts between the armed
forces of the two countries have been frequently made.
</P>
<P>
He said that to maintain good Sino-French relations will
benefit not only the two countries, but also world peace,
stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Fu Quanyou arrived in France Sunday for an official visit at
the invitation of Chief of Staff of the French Armed Forces
Jean-Philippe Douin. 
</P>
