<HEADLINE> China to Build A Green Corridor Along Beijing-Kowloon Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- China will build a 2536 km long
green corridor by planting trees on both sides of the
Beijing-Kowloon Railway over the next four years.
</P>
<P>
The project, sponsored by the National Greening Committee, the
Ministry of Forestry, the National Committee of the Communist
Youth Colleague and the Ministry of Railway, started today and is
expected to be finished by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The Agricultural Bank of China has donated one million yuan
(about 120,000 US dollars) to the effort.
</P>
<P>
According to Xu Youfang, Minister of Forestry, all the
villages, hills, waste land, highways and river banks within three
to five kilometers of the railway will be afforested.
</P>
<P>
"When the project is finished, a green tie will link Hong Kong
and the nation's capital together," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
