<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Orders Full Government Reorganization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
signed a decree on government reorganization today, effectively
telling Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and his first deputy
Anatoly Chubais to form a new cabinet, a senior government
official said.
</P>
<P>
Government information official Igor Shabdurasulov said the
decree stipulates that the government should have only one first
deputy prime minister, namely Anatoly Chubais, who was appointed
to the post last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The decree said the number of deputy prime ministers would be
cut from the current figure of nine. The number of ministries --
and of ministers -- would also be cut and some of the ministries
reorganized.
</P>
<P>
It did not give any names and did not order a formal
resignation of the government.
</P>
<P>
But according to Itar-Tass news agency, the cabinet head will
submit proposals concerning the replacement of first vice prime
ministers and vice prime ministers.
</P>
<P>
This will affect the present first vice prime ministers Alexei
Bolshakov, Viktor Ilyushin and Vladimir Potanin.
</P>
<P>
Shabdurasulov said the president only appointed the leaders of
the federal bodies of power and all other cabinet posts will be
decided by the head of government himself. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
