<HEADLINE> Sajjad Calls for Strengthened Ties with Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Senate Chairman
Wasim Sajjad today called for further widening the scope of
bilateral cooperation between Pakistan and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting here today with visiting First Under Secretary
of the Egyptian Foreign Ministry, Mohammad Adel El-Safty, Sajjad
stressed the need for further strengthening the Pakistani-Egyptian
ties through close cooperation and understanding on major regional
and international issues.
</P>
<P>
They discussed a wide range of issues of mutual interest
including the Middle East situation and the Palestine-Israel
agreement, according to a press release by the Senate.
</P>
<P>
Sajjad called in particular for increasing bilateral trade
between the two countries, saying that although trade between
Pakistan and Egypt has increased manifold in recent years, it was
still not reflective of the level of political ties between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Both sides expressed satisfaction at the fact that the
Extradition Treaty, concluded between Pakistan and Egypt in 1994,
was working very well in meeting the contemplated ends.
</P>
<P>
El-Safty said the Egyptian people and government were also
eager to further strengthen the mutually beneficial relations
between the two countries in various fields.  
</P>
</TEXT>
