<HEADLINE> Graf to Have Knee Examination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Steffi Graf, out of action for more
than a month with a knee injury, will undergo an examination this
week or next, a spokesman for the player said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Graf is set to be replaced as world number one by Switzerland's
Martina Hingis on March 31 after a total of 377 weeks at the top.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from Reuter, Graf, world number one since
June 12, 1995, is hoping to make a comeback at the end of April in
the German Open tournament in Hamburg.
</P>
<P>
"But even that can really be decided only after her next
examination," her spokesman Pascal Zimmer said.
</P>
<P>
"Her left knee will be examined at the end of this week or the
beginning of next week and then we will know more."
</P>
<P>
Graf, 27, has not played since the semifinals of a tournament
in Tokyo on February 1. 
</P>
