<HEADLINE> Panel Held in Memory of Veteran Union Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Federation of Trade
Unions held a discussion today at the Great Hall of the People in
Beijing to commemorate the 100th anniversary of Zhang Hao, a
veteran leader of the Chinese workers' movement.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, Member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
and Wei Jianxing, Member of the Political Bureau and the
Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, who formerly went by the name Lin Yuying, joined the CPC
in 1922 and was a prominent leader of the Chinese workers'
movement. He died of illness on March 6, 1942.
</P>
<P>
Wei, who is also president of the federation, made a keynote
speech at the meeting, calling on Party members to learn from
Zhang, who devoted his life to the Party and the liberation cause
of the working class, so that they can also play an important role
in the great cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Wei stressed that the status of workers must be fully respected
as the guiding force in the current reform, opening-up and
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
At present, he stressed, special attention must be paid to
enterprises that are in financial trouble.
</P>
<P>
He said that trade unions at all levels should show concern for
workers' troubles and daily life in order to unite them around the
Party and the government and to carry out the enterprise reform,
step up the economic development and safeguard social stability.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
