<HEADLINE> Bank Maintaining Stable Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The Citic Industrial Bank
established 10 years ago will strive to maintain stable business
growth this year, the bank's president Dou Jianzhong said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Serving mainly the large and medium-sized state-owned
enterprises, foreign-funded companies and major township-run
enterprises, the bank has been expanding business quickly over the
past few years, Dou said at a ceremony held here today for the
publication of the book, titled "Currency Options Guide."
</P>
<P>
The bank's profit hit 15.8 billion yuan last year, placing
Citic sixth among the country's commercial banks, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said Citic will achieve its goal by improving management
and routine banking services. A developed computer banking system
will go into trial operation next month to enhance Citic's
competitiveness with other banks, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Competition is part of life," Dou said, adding that the bank
will issue its Citic Card in the third quarter of this year, to
vie with other cards in the market.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Buchmann, head of the Beijing Office of the Credit Suisse
First Boston that co-sponsored the publication of the book with
Citic Industrial Bank, said that the Chinese-English version of
the guidebook was published at a time when China's financial
market is growing rapidly and the involvement of Chinese entities
in the international market is growing.
</P>
<P>
In line with such developments, there is an increasing demand
for financial derivatives, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese borrowers and issuers in the international capital
market have in the past decade actively used new financial
options, including those for currency, to hedge against adverse
market risks and to lower borrowing costs, Buchmann said.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss-based bank now has three branches and offices in
China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
