<HEADLINE> National Unity, Stability Emphasized at Tea Party  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- A tea party was held tonight for
deputies to fifth session of the National People's Congress (NPC)
and members of the fifth session of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, the country's
legislature and top advisory body.
</P>
<P>
The tea party, which was chaired by Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairman
of the CPPCC National Committee and head of the United Front Work
Department of the CPC Central Committee, was attended by the
Communist Party and State leaders#,including Jiang Zemin, Li Peng,
Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, Liu Huaqing and Hu Jintao.
</P>
<P>
Tomur Dawamat, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee,
addressed the party.
</P>
<P>
He cited China as a unified, multi-nationality socialist
country and said that the CPC has always attached great importance
to the issues and work concerning various ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The first generation of the central collective leadership
represented by Mao Zedong formulated a series of principles and
policies on settlement of China's issues relating to different
ethnic groups, he said.
</P>
<P>
Since the Third Plenum of the 11th Central Committee held in
late 1978, the second generation of the central collective
leadership with Deng Xiaoping at the core made important
expositions on the issues and work concerning ethnic groups in
leading China's reform, opening-up and socialist modernization
construction, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tomur Dawamat noted that Deng Xiaoping's stand, viewpoints and
methods on handling China's issues relating to ethnic minority
groups during the new historical period constitute important
component contents of Deng's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The third generation of the central collective leadership with
Jiang Zemin at the core has inherited and carried forward the fine
traditions and work styles of the leaders of the Party's older
generations, attached overriding importance to the issues and work
concerning the ethnic groups and to equality, unity and common
prosperity among nationalities throughout the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
Unity among all ethnic groups, social stability, economic
development, consolidated boundary and a significantly improved
life of the people have fully proven that the Chinese nation has a
great allying power, the Party's policy on ethnic issues are
correct and successful, the work relating to ethnic groups is
effective, and the relations among all ethnic groups are very
good, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
