<HEADLINE> Computerized Credit Rating System for Card Holders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 11 (Xinhua) -- A computerized rating network
to assess the credibility of all applicants and guarantors for the
Peony credit card went into operation today in Shanghai, China's
financial and industrial powerhouse,
</P>
<P>
The system will uncover fraudulent applications and credit card
use, and reduce the financial risk of card holders, said
a representative with the Shanghai Criminalistics Society.
</P>
<P>
The network was jointly developed by the association and the
Shanghai Branch of the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
The Peony Card is a credit card issued by the Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China, one of China's major commercial banks,
and has nearly 400,000 holders here.
</P>
<P>
The card registered a transaction volume of more than 15
billion yuan in Shanghai last year, with the accumulative amount
reaching 100 billion yuan. 
