<HEADLINE> Chinese Table Tennis Teams Starts Training Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, northern China, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese
national men's and women's table tennis teams started a one-month
training camp here on Tuesday to prepare for title defences next
month's world championships in Manchester.
</P>
<P>
China, which had a clean sweep of all seven titles at last
championships at Tianjin, China, in 1995, is facing serious
challenge in the men's events, said men's team coach Cai Zhenhua.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot say we would definitively win the men's team title,"
said Cai. "But we would try our best."
</P>
<P>
Thirty of the country's top men table tennis players and 28 of
the women elite have arrived here, including world titlists Kong
Linghui, Wang Tao and Liu Guoliang.
</P>
<P>
Coaches said they have not decided the lineups for the
championships but hope the camp will help improve the techniques
and mental quality of the younger players. 
