<HEADLINE> Symposium on Deng Xiaoping's Theoretical Contributions Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- A seminar discussing the
significant contributions made by the late Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping to the theory of scientific socialism was held in Beijing
today.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was sponsored by the Teaching and Research
Department under the Party School of the Communist Party of China
Central Committee and the Editorial Board of the magazine, "Front
for Theoretical Work."
</P>
<P>
Participants spoke highly of Deng's contributions to the theory
of scientific socialism, noting that his greatest contribution was
the creation of the theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
This theory is of great importance to the history of scientific
socialism and takes hold of the essence of socialism, they said,
adding that it offers the first series of fundamental ideas on how
to build, consolidate and develop socialism in an economically and
culturally underdeveloped country like China, they said.
</P>
<P>
Guided by the theory, the Party formulated its principal line
in the early stages of socialism, made the historic decision to
undertake the reform and opening-up, mapped out the blueprint for
China's socialism, and put forward the theory on the socialist
market economy.
</P>
<P>
The participants termed Deng's theory as contemporary Marxism
in China and an important symbol for the development of socialism
in a new age. 
</P>
</TEXT>
