<HEADLINE> Belgian Bank Granted Bank License in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Generale Bank (GB) of Belgium
has been granted a banking license by the Monetary Authority under
the Banking Ordinance, a spokesman for the Hong Kong Monetary
Authority said here today.
</P>
<P>
As the largest banking institution in Belgium and ranking 78th
in the world in terms of tier 1 capital, the GB group provides
full-services banking through its 1,100 domestic branches and
international network of subsidiaries, branches and representative
offices around the world including New York, Tokyo, Beijing,
Shanghai and Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
A full branch will enable GB to maintain its global treasury
activities on a 24-hour basis by operating in financial markets of
Hong Kong, Brussels and New York.
</P>
<P>
After the granting of a banking license to GB, the number of
licensed banks in Hong Kong has increased to 183, in addition to
366 restricted license banks and deposit-taking companies.
</P>
