<HEADLINE> Tung Names Commission on Remuneration for HKSAR Councils </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa today
announced the appointment of the Independent Commission on
Remuneration for members of the Executive Council and the
Legislature of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The Independent Commission will be chaired by Wong Po Yan with
Lau Siu Kai, Thomas Leung, Anthony Wu, Chan Bing Woon and Payson
Cha as members.
</P>
<P>
The commission will serve a two-year term, from March 12, 1997,
to March 31, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that the commission will undertake the task of making
recommendations, on the basis of the existing system, on the
remuneration for members of the Executive Council, the Provisional
Legislative Council and the First Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
He said that the commission should also recommend whether
there should be any changes after July 1 to the remuneration
packages for members of the Executive Council and the Provisional
Legislature, adding: "It should complete its deliberations as soon
as possible before July 1."
</P>
<P>
On his appointment of Wong as the chairman of the commission,
Tung said he was sure that with his experience and a wide range
of public service, Wong will be able to guide the commission in
coming up with fair and reasonable recommendations within its
terms of reference.
</P>
<P>
He said that in view of the tight time-frame and the range of
issues to be considered, the commission will start work as soon as
possible, with secretariat support to be provided by the Chief
Executive's office. 
</P>
