<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> s d s 3206 China-Law-Severity of Law China to Maintain Legal Deterrence Against Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- A new criminal code in China is
to maintain, in the main, the level of severity in punishing
criminals as is found in the existing Criminal Law and 22
supplementary laws and decisions, legal experts said here today.
</P>
<P>
Draft amendments to the Criminal Law, which have kept the
majority of sentencing provisions unchanged, are now under review
by deputies to the National People's Congress (NPC), China's top
legislature in session since March 1.
</P>
<P>
The draft amendments have been a result of wide-ranging
discussions and in-depth researches by people from all walks of
life.
</P>
<P>
There has been a long-going debate on the proper level of
severity in punishing criminals among Chinese legal experts, law
enforcers and the public.
</P>
<P>
Some people in academic circles have proposed light treatment
of criminals, reducing capital punishment sentences or even
abolishing capital punishment, in accordance with the world trend
of meting out light punishment for the convicted.
</P>
<P>
But judicial bodies and the public are more concerned about
worsening public security, and believe that it is still too early
to adopt such a scholarly proposal.
</P>
<P>
According to an official with the Legislative Work Subcommittee
under the NPC Standing Committee, judging by what public opinions
the NPC has received so far, the Chinese public favors giving
harsher punishments against offenders.
</P>
<P>
Many NPC deputies also support heavier treatment of offenders
who jeopardize public security and market economic order.
</P>
<P>
Although China remains one of the countries with the lowest
crime rates, there has been a fairly rapid increase in crimes; and
economic crimes, corruption and malfeasance have been going up
speedily, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Gao Mingxuan, secretary-general of the Criminal Law Chapter
of the China Law Society, said that the top legislature has
attached great importance to the issue of punishment severity.
</P>
<P>
Wang Hanbin, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, has
organized many meetings and seminars to solicit opinions and
discuss this issue before a consensus was finally reached -- to
maintain the severity of sentences largely unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The main reasons are: the consistency and stability of the
criminal justice system must be maintained; and deterrence against
wrong-doers must be kept to curb the rise in crimes in the
country, according to Gao.
</P>
<P>
The draft amendments stipulate that the severity of punishment
must be commensurate with the offender's crime and his or her
criminal responsibility.
</P>
<P>
Gao went on to explain that the relatively harsh treatments in
the draft law are directed against crimes that severely harm state
security and people's interests. Crimes normally regarded as
"contradictions among the people," such as crimes committed out of
neglect, are usually given sentences that last no more than three
years and never exceed seven years according to the draft
amendments.
</P>
<P>
Most deputies attending the current NPC session agreed that the
severity of punishment in the draft law is suitable to
Chinese realities and is proper and adequate.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970311.0084 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Azerbaijan Ambassador Praises Bilateral Ties with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Azerbaijan Ambassador to China
Tamerlan Karayev spoke highly of Sino-Azerbaijan relations
recently on the occasion of the fifth anniversary of the sealing
of diplomatic ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"The ancient silk road which bridged the eastern and western
civilizations has regained its vigor to help reinforce the
cooperation between Azerbaijan and China," Karayev said during a
recent interview with Xinhua News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The friendly contacts between people of the two nations can be
traced back to ancient times, Karayev said, and since the
forging of diplomatic ties, their cooperation in political,
economic, cultural and educational sectors has grown stronger.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the frequent exchange of high-level visits
has laid a sound foundation for the improvement of the traditional
friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador expressed his thanks for China's support to the
economic construction in Azerbaijan, promising broad prospects for
bilateral cooperation in such fields as geological prospecting,
petroleum recovering and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
As a permanent member of the UN Security Council, China is
playing a significant role in the international arena, Karayev
said.
</P>
<P>
China's principle of mutual respect for sovereignty and
territorial integrity, non-interference in each other's internal
affairs, its opposition to separatism of any form, and equality
among countries, big or small, have been widely supported by the
people of Azerbaijan and all peace-loving people of the world, he
noted.  
