<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Legislators on National Defense Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- It is necessary to enshrine
principles and policies set forth by the Party for the People's
Liberation Army and the army's fine traditions and precious
experience in the form of law, so as to help strengthen China's
national defense.
</P>
<P>
This is a consensus reached by legislators here attending the
Fifth Session of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC),
China's legislature, who are deliberating on a draft law on
national defense these days.
</P>
<P>
They held that the draft law draws historical experience of the
past decades since the founding of New China in 1949 and reflects
developments and features in the new historical period. It is a
socialist defense law with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
They noted that, if adopted at the current NPC session, the law
will play a significant role in building and consolidating
national defense, safeguarding a smooth progression of reform and
opening up as well as national economic development, and ensuring
the country's long-term stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Legislator Feng Wencheng from east China's Anhui Province said
that the draft national defense law has three distinct
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
"The law has affirmed the Party's absolute leadership over the
armed forces, stressed the importance of popular education on
national defense, and provided legal protection for the legitimate
rights and interests of servicemen," he said.
</P>
<P>
Pan Yiqing, a legislator from north China's Tianjin, said that,
while adhering to the Party's leadership over the army, the draft
law defines different responsibilities of the Central Military
Commission and the State Council, and clearly stipulates on
national defense funds, national defense assets, the obligations
and rights of servicemen, scientific research for national
defense, and weapons production.
</P>
<P>
Lawmakers also put forth ideas and suggestions for improving
the draft law.
</P>
<P>
Gong Pingqiu, a PLA deputy to the NPC, said that the Party's
absolute leadership over the army is the fundamental principle for
the building of the PLA and, therefore, should be made still
clearer in the draft law.
</P>
<P>
Anhui legislator Meng Fulin stressed that, in the process of
carrying out reform and opening up and seeking prosperity,
national defense should by no means be neglected.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that the law stipulate clearly on the proper
settlement of and financial support for soldiers and officers
disabled in wars and military service, and that specific
punishments be stipulated for those who refuse to serve in the
army.
</P>
<P>
Legislator Feng Wencheng said that the system of the armed
police force should be established in the form of law.
</P>
<P>
Legislator Wang Peisheng from Shanghai suggested that the draft
law add some articles concerning the training of PLA men with both
military and civil skills, so as to enable ex-servicemen to better
serve the country's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
After being revised according to the legislators' suggestions,
the draft national defense law will be put to a vote at the last
plenum of the current NPC session.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970311.0092 </DOCNO>
