<HEADLINE> Chinese Girl Gets Letter, Photo from Belarussian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- A 12-year-old Chinese girl who
has won international recognition for her paintings today received
a thank-you letter and photo from Belarussian President Alexandr
Lukashenko.
</P>
<P>
At a presentation ceremony here today, Zeng Yangyang, who
attends the Lixin Primary School of Beijing, was given the letter
and photo by Belarussian Ambassador to China Vyachaslau
N. Kuznyatsou, in appreciation for the New-Year's card and
painting she sent to Lukashenko last year.
</P>
<P>
Zeng's painting to Lukashenko is of a giant panda and
peonies. In her card, she invited the president to visit Beijing.
</P>
<P>
In his letter, the Belarussian president says, "In China, which
is far away from Belarus, someone is concerned about our country
and wants to make friends with us. I am deeply moved. This wish
has also been strongly echoed in my heart. Thank you very much for
inviting me to visit Beijing."
</P>
<P>
"Children of all countries share a common aspiration -- peace
and friendship," he writes.
</P>
<P>
After reading the president's letter, Zeng said that she wants
to meet young people in Belarus, especially those mentioned by the
president in his letter who are suffering from the aftereffects of
the nuclear disaster at the Chernobyl Nuclear Power Plant. Zeng
said she wants to send them paintings, too.
</P>
<P>
At the ceremony, the Belarussian ambassador said that since the
two countries forged diplomatic ties in 1992, they have seen
sustained development of cooperation in political, economic and
cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
He said Lukashenko's letter and photo to Zeng reflect his great
concern for the friendship and exchanges between young people of
the two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador called Zeng a "sincere young envoy" of the
friendship between Belarussian and Chinese peoples. 
</P>
</TEXT>
