<HEADLINE> Abducted Germans Freed in Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The seven German tourists kidnapped
in Yemen a week ago were released following efforts by the Yemeni
government, said German Foreign Ministry spokesman Martin Erdmann
here today.
</P>
<P>
According to Erdmann, the seven people were well and would be
taken to the Yemeni capital of Sanaa by helicopter later today.
</P>
<P>
The Germans, aged between 30 and 45, were in Yemen on a
motorcycling holiday. They were seized by a gang of about 30 men
near the border with Oman last Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three years, members of rival clans in Yemen had
kidnapped 80 foreigners to press for various demands and extort
ransom from the Yemeni government in Sanaa.
</P>
<P>
In all the cases, the kidnapped were freed unharmed. 
</P>
