<HEADLINE> Another Tourism Street for Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- A street lined with travel
agencies will open in mid-May in Beijing's Chaoyang District,
making it the second such site in the Chinese capital following
the Beijing Tourism Street.
</P>
<P>
The Chaoyang tourism street, located next to Chaoyang Park,
features European-style buildings, and a combined floor space of
5,200 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The street can accommodate more than 50 travel services. Each
space of about nine sq m will be rented at an annual cost of
25,000 yuan, according Wang Yuying, director of the tourism and
foreign affairs office of Chaoyang District.
</P>
<P>
The main structure of the street has been built, and several
travel agencies have booked offices there, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
The project will provide convenience for Beijing people to
travel, and will also help local travel services to expand
business, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
