<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Set up Electoral Tribunal Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria will soon set up a
tribunal to try politicians accused of malpractices in the
impending local government elections on party basis scheduled to
begin on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Justice Mamman Nasir, Chairman of the Transition
Implementation Committee, disclosed this on Monday in Kogi State
in central Nigeria while meeting local political leaders.
</P>
<P>
He blamed the shortage of voters' cards in the just-ended
voters' registrations on malpracticing politicians, saying that
they have not learnt much from the country's past electoral
experiences.
</P>
<P>
He reminded Nigerians that it was in the anarchy state
triggered off by the country's last election that General Sani
Abacha took the power.
</P>
<P>
Nasir's Transition Implementation Committee is one of the
several official agencies set up by General Abacha to moniter his
transition to civil rule program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
