<HEADLINE> Mozambican Police Arrests 112 Illegal Smugglers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican police has during
the last three days arrested 112 illegal smugglers, among whom 20
are aliens, local newspapers Noticias reported here today.
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Abilio Quive said the police, who operated
mainly in the living quarters, hotels and markets, also recovered
three guns, 33 vehicles and many electronic gadgets.
</P>
<P>
He said the foreign smugglers, who were illegal immigrants
from Tanzania, Burundi, Nigeria, Zaire and Pakistan, were also
involved in the trafficking of drugs, arms, cars, among others.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the campaign against crime would continue
in the country to "clean" the social environment in the southern
African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
