<HEADLINE> Velasco Takes Gold at Italian Boxing Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Filipino boxer Roel Velasco beat
his Turkish opponent Denizmusa to win the light flyweight gold
medal at an international boxing meet in Italy last weekend,
newspapers here reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Velasco, 24, was a bronze medalist at the Barcelona Olympic
Games in 1992. His brother Mansueto Velasco won an Olympic silver
at Atlanta last summer.
</P>
<P>
Velasco's gold on Sunday was the only one for the Philippines,
which was ranked third on the medal table at the Italian meet with
one gold, one bantamweight silver and bronzes in featherweight,
lightweight and welterweight events, the newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
Host Italy topped the medal table with six golds, followed by
second-placed Ukraine at two golds and one silver.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen countries took part in the eight-day meet which began
on March 3 and concluded on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The newspapers said the Filipino boxing team will participate
in at least nine international events this year.
</P>
<P>
They include the King's Cup invitational meet slated in April
in Bangkok, the South East Asian Games in Jakarta in October and
the World Boxing Championships in Budapest, Hungary, in the same
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
