<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan President Makes Key Appointments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan President Nursultan
Nazarbayev has appointed Zeinukka Kakimzanov as the new deputy
chairman of the Supreme Economic Committee (SEC), the Kazakhstan
newspaper Pravda said here today.
</P>
<P>
Kakimzanov, born in 1959, was graduated from Moscow University
and had worked as chairman of the board of the People's Savings
Bank.
</P>
<P>
Former SEC Deputy Chairman Erdjan Ujembaev was named as the
director of the newly-established National Strategic Planning
Office (NSPO).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Nazarbayev appointed Galymzan Zakiyanov as the
director of the National Strategic Supervision Office (NSSO),
another newly-established organization.
</P>
<P>
The SEC, which was set up in April last year and headed by
Nazarbayev himself, mainly serves as an advisory body for the
president on strategies of economic and social development as well
as national security.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev issued a decree on structural reform of the state
administration last Tuesday, cutting half of the number of
government organizations.
</P>
<P>
Two new organizations -- the NSPO and the NSSO -- were created
and put under direct control of the president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
