<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Meets US Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
told a US business delegation here this afternoon that China will
do even more to carry out its policy of reform and opening to the
outside world.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the policy, initiated by the late Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping, has brought enormous tangible benefits to the
Chinese people, and therefore will not, cannot and should not be
changed.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks during his meeting with a group from the
US-China Business Council, headed by its Chairman Donald Staheli.
</P>
<P>
He said that it has been proved that the third generation of
the collective leadership of the Chinese Communist Party with
Jiang Zemin at the core is capable of better implementing the
reform and opening-up policy.
</P>
<P>
On Sino-US trade ties, the vice-premier said that the Chinese
economy, the biggest developing one, and the US economy, the
biggest developed one, are strongly complementary and have huge
untapped potential.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes the two countries would strengthen their trade
and economic cooperation in order to push forward the overall
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Staheli said that his council, formed by US business leaders in
1973 to promote US business ties with China, will continue to help
US companies to expand their business in China and strive for a
comprehensive growth of US-China relations.
</P>
<P>
The delegation came to China at the invitation of the China
Council for Promoting International Trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
