<HEADLINE> Zanzibar Launches Sustainable Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Programme (UNDP) resident representative and
coordinator in Tanzania, Victor Angelo, has signed an agreement
of the launching of the Zanzibar Sustainable Project.
</P>
<P>
Zanzibar Finance Minister Amina Salum Ali signed the agreement
on behalf of the Zanzibar government at a function held in
Zanzibar on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Angelo said UNDP supported Tanzania's efforts at social and
economic development.
</P>
<P>
He added the Isles sustainable project was aimed at creating
partnerships between different institutions and strengthening the
environment management program.
</P>
<P>
He further said Zanzibar town has been selected as one of the
project areas in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Angelo also appealed to the Islanders to participate through
different means in sustaining the project to enable it record a
success story.
</P>
<P>
The project, framed under the umbrella of "sustainable city
program", undertake globally to localize Agenda 21 and the 1996
Habitat Agenda adopted in Istanbul of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The project is part of the national replication process in
Tanzania which is based on the local institution co-ordination,
national and international partnership. 
</P>
</TEXT>
