<HEADLINE> Two Kilograms Heroin Seized at Kenya's Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan police have seized two
kilograms of heroin at the Jom Kenyatta International Airport,
the Daily Nation reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted sources of the Anti-Narcotics Unit as saying
on Monday that the consignment was seized from three Nigerians
and a Tanzanian.
</P>
<P>
The suspects arrested last week were being held at the police
unit at the airport and would be charged in court once
investigations are completed, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The four foreigners were arrested last week soon after
disembarking from an aircraft from an Asian country as police
officers detected that they had swallowed the drugs.
</P>
<P>
The sources pointed out that "our men at the airport are very
alert and attention is being focused on the airlines arriving
from drug-source countries."
</P>
<P>
The anti-narcotics officers in Kenya had arrested eight
Nigerian drug barons at the airport since last December including
one suspected to operate an international drug trafficking ring.
</P>
<P>
Late in 1995, a woman passenger traveling from India was
arrested at the airport with 10 kilograms of heroin worth a
street value of 180,000 U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Kenya had intensified the war against
drugs by ensuring that aircraft arriving from drug-source
countries were thoroughly checked before being cleared.
</P>
<P>
"Curbing drug trafficking is an enormous task since the drug
barons have devised deceptive methods of transporting the
consignment", the sources added. 
</P>
