decision was unconstitutional.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that he had been in his parliamentary office on
Monday attending to businesses, and would take his seat regularly
when the Assembly meets on Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Makwetu was charged of fostering tribalism and divisions in
the party and of subverting the leadership of the Stanley Mogoba,
who succeeded him as PAC president late last year. 
