<HEADLINE> China to Improve Risk Management of Foreign Debts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- China will acts to improve risk
management of its foreign debts this year in a bid to improve its
efficiency in utilizing foreign funds, according to Tuesday's
China Securities News.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that instead of the conventional practice of
imposing a foreign debt quota, China will gradually introduce an
assets-liability management system to better use overseas funds,
the newspaper quoted a foreign investment official.
</P>
<P>
A small number of large enterprise groups will be granted the
authority to raise funds overseas on their own this year, said the
official.
</P>
<P>
"Poor efficiency in managing foreign investment in some projects
resulted in defaulted debt among financial institutions, it also
posed difficulties to foreign debt control," the official said.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed to "invisible foreign debt" in infrastructural
projects and misuse of short-term foreign loans for long-term
projects.
</P>
<P>
"An assets-liability management system of foreign loans will
prove to be a wise choice for the establishment of a socialist
market economy, and China's financial institutions, which are well
under the way of commercialization, will surely benefit from
more efficient use of foreign funds," said the official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
