<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Share prices reversed their
downswing and rose sharply today on the Singapore market, as the
benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index gained 22.27 points to
close at 2,194.75 points.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 228.45 million units, worth
510.06 million Singapore dollars (about 359.2 million US dollars).
Advances overwhelmed declines by 246 to 92, while 268 other
counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Ber Ind. was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 14.51 million units. It was followed by MBF Holdings
which had 8.31 million of shares traded. Promet was next with 7.63
million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 70 cents to finish at 28.7 Singapore
dollars. Local car dealer Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) gained 60 cents
to end at 15 Singapore dollars, while drinks and food maker F&AMP;N
closed 50 cents higher at 13.3 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.2 Singapore dollars to end at 16.1 Singapore
dollars. M Cement fell by 88 cents to 2.94 Singapore dollars,
while Keppel FELS was 60 cents lower at 5.15 Singapore dollars.
</P>
