<HEADLINE> "For a Green China" Drive Goes on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Action to reforest China was
urged by the National Green Committee and the Ministry of Forestry
today-- one day before China's 19th "Tree-Planting Day."
</P>
<P>
According to Zhu Guangyao, Vice-Minister of Forestry, large
scale tree-planting work has started across the country from
south to north.
</P>
<P>
In 16 provinces such as Guangdong and Sichuan, more than 1.5
million hectares of land have been leveled for tree-planting,
show initial statistics.
</P>
<P>
In Zhejiang, Guizhou and Hunan provinces, half of the total
tree-planting task has been completed.
</P>
<P>
According to the state plan, by the year 2000 the forest
coverage in China will reach 15.5 percent, and the vegetation
coverage in urban areas will reach 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Advocated by China's former leader Deng Xiaoping and supported
by the central government, the national tree-planting drive in
China has planted 34.25 million hectares of forestry since its
inception 19 years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
