<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Warm Weather Comes to Shanghai Early This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Statistics from the Shanghai
meteorological Bureau show that the city's average temperature
between March 1 and 10 reached an unprecedented 12 degrees Celsius.
</P>
<P>
According to Shi Youhao, an official with the bureau, the
temperature was the highest since the metropolis began weather
records in 1873.
</P>
<P>
The temperature was equivalent to previous years' early April.
</P>
<P>
In the history of Shanghai, only three years-- 1935, 1960, and
1966-- have had average temperatures of the first ten days of
March exceed ten degrees Celsius.
</P>
<P>
The warm weather this year was caused by weak cold air flow
from the north and strong warm and humid air flow from the south,
according to weather experts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
