<HEADLINE> Identity Card to be Issued in Tanzania by Next </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Every Tanzanian will be
issued with an identity card by next June in order to
differentiate citizens from non-citizens effective this year, Dar
es Salaam Regional Commissioner Hassan Ngwilizi has announced.
</P>
<P>
"Every adult citizen will be issued with an identity card
regardless of his or her occupation, only children will not be
provided with one," Ngwilizi told reporters on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He said even farmers in villages will have to possess identity
#ards.
</P>
<P>
According to the Dar es Salaam regional commissioner, the
decision was made by the government two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Billions of Tanzania Shillings will be required to print the
cards, added the regional commissioner. 
