<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, March 11 (Xinhua) -- A panel consisting 20-odd
experts, as well as officials from central and local governments,
got together here today to discuss proposals for the construction
of a highway bridge linking the western part of Shenzhen and Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Entrusted by the State Planning Commission, China International
Engineering Consulting Corporation presided over the meeting,
which will last for six days.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, Shenzhen plans to build a
thoroughfare in its western areas, which will include the
construction of a five-km-long highway bridge across the sea from
Dongjiaotou of Shekou, Shenzhen to Yuen Long of Hong Kong, and
building a new port covering 50 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The project has been listed by the Ministry of Communications
and Shenzhen City as a key construction program during the Ninth
Five-Year-Plan period (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
The completion of the project will advance economic cooperation
between Shenzhen and Hong Kong, helping maintain Hong Kong's
prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong businessmen have invested 7.6 billion U.S. dollars in
Shenzhen, accounting for 64 percent of Shenzhen's total overseas
investment. 
