<HEADLINE> Central China Province Has More Foreign Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Foreign-funded firms have
become a vital part of economic development of central China's
Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government approved 4,900 foreign-funded
enterprises by the end of last October.
</P>
<P>
Of the 3,340 registered firms, 2,676, or 81 percent of the
total, were joint ventures, 119 were cooperative firms, 392 were
exclusively foreign-funded firms and 153 were foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
They cover a wide range of trades including textiles, garment,
chemistry, building material and machine-building.
</P>
<P>
One third of these firms involved an investment of more than
one million US dollars each. Some 2,250 firms, or 67 percent of
the total, were small ones with an investment below one million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The provincial capital, Zhengzhou, has attracted 40 percent of
the overseas investment. 
</P>
