<HEADLINE> Northwest Shaanxi Accelerates Opening Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi Province
has witnessed an unprecedented momentum in its opening drive,
thanks to new measures by the local government.
</P>
<P>
Under the guidance of "promoting development through
opening-up," the province introduced some 1.53 billion US dollars
of contractual overseas funds by the end of last year through trade
fairs.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Shaanxi approved some 250 overseas-funded projects and
made actual use of 510 million dollars in foreign capital.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Shaanxi provincial foreign trade and
economic cooperation office said new measures to usher in foreign
funds had taken the province's opening drive to a more extensive
and deeper level.
</P>
<P>
Along with the transfer of shares in a power plant and the
contract to manage an expressway last year, new mechanisms were
initially installed to introduce overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
And the structure of its foreign investment was more
diversified last year, said the official, adding that
infrastructural facilities and basic industries have become
hotbeds for overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
In addition, more overseas investments are channelled into
productive projects, which are crucial to the inland province's
economic take-off. 
</P>
