<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Stonetech Exhibition Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- A total of over 150 businesses
from more than a dozen countries and regions today displayed their
latest technologies and stone products at the Stonetech Exhibition
which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises from Italy, Portugal, Finland, Greece, Spain, the
United States, India, Canada, the Republic of Korea, as well as
from Hong Kong and Taiwan have participated in the exhibition,
co-sponsored by the China State Administration of Building
Materials Industry and the China Chamber of International
Commerce (CCIC).
</P>
<P>
According to senior CCIC official Liu Jingzhou, the expanding
cooperation between stone enterprises from different countries has
vigorously boosted the industry development.
</P>
<P>
China's export volume of stone topped a record 700 million US
dollars in 1996. So far, China has found markets for its stone
products in Japan, the Republic of Korea, Germany, the United
States, Russia, Thailand, Indonesia, Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China has introduced a large amount of advanced
equipment from Italy, Germany and other countries. By drawing on
advanced foreign technology, China has developed equipment which
conforms to the country's stone production needs.
</P>
<P>
To date, China has set up over 100 equipment manufacturing
enterprises for stone production. Starting in 1990, China has
exported equipment for stone production to Russia, Kazakhstan,
Pakistan, Indonesia and Hungary.
</P>
<P>
China produced 100 million sq m of stone materials including
granite, marble and terrazzo in 1996, ranking behind Italy as the
world's second-largest producer of stone, the official added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
