<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-11 09:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Political Group Formed in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 11 (Xinhua) -- A non-government political
party consisting of personages in Kuwait has been formed in
disregard of the official rejection of such organizations in the
Islamic Gulf country.
</P>
<P>
The new group, called the Kuwait Society for the Defense of
Public Fund, announced its formation Monday afternoon at a meeting
attended by some 200 of its members which include some former
parliamentary members, prominent businessmen and intellectuals.
</P>
<P>
The group, which was designed to help check corruption,
applied to Kuwaiti Ministry of Social Affairs and Labour for
official recognition, local newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
Under the current law, the Kuwaiti government has suspended the
formation of any Non-Governmental organizations. However, such
groups do exist in fact without official recognition.
</P>
<P>
Sources of the new group were quoted as saying "the time is
right for such a movement (to defense public funds) to come out
and represent the moderates" in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the constitution of the society, one of the basic
objectives is to protect public funds, through awareness,
education, preparation of studies, bills, and also to investigate
certain cases regarding embezzlements of public funds.
</P>
<P>
Its constitution defined public funds as "all funds owned by
the state and its establishments, and other companies where the
government has at least 25 percent of their shares."
</P>
<P>
The sources said the society does not mean to confront anyone
or anything and advocates a free market economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970311.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-11 09:43 </DATE_TIME>
