<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Set Up National Internet Control Board </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnamese government has
decided to set up a board to control and coordinate the operation
and development of the Internet in the country, the local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The board is tasked to coordinate operations by ministries,
branches and localities in the formation, management and expansion
of Internet operations and services and to control, develop and
appraise policies and projects on information exchange on the net.
</P>
<P>
The minister of science, technology and environment will be the
board chairman and the general director of the directorate general
of posts and telecommunications will be the vice chairman.
</P>
<P>
Members of the board will include leading officials of the
ministries of culture and information, interior, and education and
training, the national steering board on information technology
and the national center for natural science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The government has also issued a decree to promulgate a
24-article provisional regulation on the establishment, management
and use of the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Under the regulations, the government will control the
operations, services and entry gates to the internet in Vietnam as
well as the content of information circulated on the net.
</P>
<P>
All agencies, organizations and businesses must base their
servers in Vietnam when connecting computer networks to the
Internet, and bear full responsibility for the content of the
information they disseminate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
