<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Petro-Chemical Center Taking Shape in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Maoming City in south China's
Guangdong Province is striving to become a petro-chemical
production base generating three billion yuan of output value
yearly by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The city has been accelerating construction of an oil refinery
with an annual processing capacity of 10 million tons, since the
operation of a 300,000-ton ethylene production facility in the
city in February, said a local official.
</P>
<P>
A heavy-oil catalytic cracker, with a processing capacity of
1.2 million tons, one of the key projects during the Ninth
Five-Year-Plan period (1996-2000), reported a success on trial
processing in October last year.
</P>
<P>
By the year of 2000, the city will have an oil refining
capacity of 1.7 million tons. Its ethylene production capacity
will be enlarged to 450,000 tons, and the annual ethylene
processing output value will amount to 10 billion yuan, said the
official.
</P>
<P>
Maoming has emerged as an industrial city for the development
of shale oil and oil refining since the 1950s.
</P>
<P>
The campaign to build this city into a petro-chemical
production center is necessary to improve the backward economic
situation of the city and western Guangdong, said the official.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the 300,000-ton ethylene project,
which cost over 17 billion yuan, will be able to provide the
market with 890,000 tons of synthetic resin, synthetic rubber and
chemical raw materials. It will also generate seven billion yuan
of output value and 600 million yuan of after-tax profits a year
while advancing the city's industrial base by adding 10 billion
yuan of industrial output value yearly and creating 100,000 new
jobs.
</P>
<P>
The city has made painstaking efforts to make the ethylene
project a complete success, including establishing a leading group
responsible for comprehensive development of the ethylene project
and related research organizations. The leading group has decided
to vigorously develop the processing industry by the immediate
consumption of ethylene by-products.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises to produce radial tires and aluminum plastic hybrid
materials have started construction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
