<HEADLINE> Iranian FM Ends Visit to Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Ali
Akbar Velayati left here this morning for the Czech Republic,
following discussions with Turkish leaders on the diplomatic
dispute between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
During his one-day stay here, Velayati conveyed an invitation
to Turkish President Suleyman Demirel from Iranian President
Hashemi Rafsanjani to attend a summit meeting of the Organization
of the Islamic Conference (OIC) scheduled in December in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Velayati also met with Turkish Prime Minister
Necmettin Erbakan and his Turkish counterpart Tansu Ciller and
exchanged views on the diplomatic dispute between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The dispute was triggered by Iranian Ambassador to Ankara
Muhammed Reza Baqeri who made a pro-Sharia (Islamic law) speech at
the commemoration of an anti-Israeli "Al-Quds (Jerusalem) Night"
gathering in the Turkish city of Sincan, 40 kilometers west of
Ankara last month.
</P>
<P>
Velayati said Monday that Iran is determined to end the
trouble which resulted in exchange of expulsions of diplomats by
both sides.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Demirel sent Foreign Ministry
Undersecretary Ali Tuygan as special envoy to Iran and handed
over a written message to Rafsanjani in order to improve the
strained ties. 
