<HEADLINE> Zambia Bans Sale of Perishable Products Without </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has banned
the sale of perishable products which do not show their expiry
dates, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Deputy Minister of Commerce, Trade and
Industry Ackim Nkole as saying that all products displayed in
shops will be required to bear expiry dates after which they
should be moved from the shelves.
</P>
<P>
A team comprising council and ministry officials has been put
on alert to effect the exercise. Retail outlet owners found not
complying with the new regulation risk their goods being
confiscated and their businesses shut, said the minister.
</P>
<P>
A drive has been launched in Zambia against the sale of
products that are under weight or without expiry dates. Minister
officials are touring the country to make measures effective.
</P>
<P>
He assured that his officials will be going to manufacturers
who are responsible for packaging to ensure that the right
weights are followed. 
</P>
