<HEADLINE> College Students Appeal to Plant Trees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Students at Beijing Forestry
University have appealed to young people across the country to
carry forward the wish of Deng Xiaoping and create a greener world.
</P>
<P>
The call is a prelude to the 16th Tree Planting Festival that
begins March 12. Students with the university said that "although
Deng has left us, the trees he planted are like banners that
inspire us to study hard, cherish our land, and contribute to the
nation's ecology."
</P>
<P>
Deng, who was an enthusiastic advocate of tree planting
nationwide, took part in tree planting in Beijing for 11
consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
The students urged fellow young people across the country to
launch a greening campaign in their schools and neighborhoods, and
take care of trees and wildlife so as to make contributions to the
sustained development of natural resources.
</P>
<P>
They also asked for efforts to spread science and technology in
the countryside, where the knowledge would be used to maintain the
ecological balance.  
</P>
