<HEADLINE> More Ethnic Minority People to Study Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, March 11 (Xinhua) -- More ethnic minority people from
northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region will go abroad
to study, according to a new policy of the central government.
</P>
<P>
The State Education Commission will give preference to Xinjiang
and other ethnic areas in sending individuals to study abroad at
public expense this year.
</P>
<P>
It is a measure to train more high-tech personnel for the
ethnic areas, said a local official. He noted that the ethnic
areas have always suffered from a scarcity of trained personnel.
</P>
