<HEADLINE> Ewing Named NBA Player of the Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Patrick Ewing of New York Knicks
today was named the NBA Player of the Week for games played from
Monay, March 3 through Sunday, March 9.
</P>
<P>
Ewing led New York to a 4-0 record as the Knicks extended their
season-high-tying winning streak to seven games with a 97-93 win
against the Chicago Bulls at Madison Square Garden on Sunday. The
7-0 center averaged 31 points, 9.8 rebounds, 1.3 assists and 1.0
blocked shots per game, while shooting 0.623 (48 for 77) from the
field. He ranked second in scoring, ninth in shooting percentage
and 18th in rebounding among league leaders for the week.
</P>
<P>
Ewing began the week on Tuesday, March 4 with 17 points and
three rebounds in a 93-86 defeat of the Milwaukee Bucks. He
followed that performance with 36 points, including the 21,000th
of his career, 13 rebounds and two blocked shots in a 100-94 win
at Toronto and had a season-high 39 points and nine rebounds in a
113-102 victory at Boston. Ewing closed out the week with 32
points and 14 rebounds in the victory over Chicago.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for NBA Player of the Week were Charlotte's
Anthony Mason and Glen Rice, Orlando's Anfernee Hardaway,
Phoenix's Kevin Johnson, Portland's Isaiah Rider, Toronto's Damon
Stoudamire and Utah's Karl Malone. 
</P>
