<HEADLINE> Sichuan Finance Officials Banned From Taking Gifts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The Sichuan Department of Finance
has adopted a new step that bans financial officials from taking
gifts or money, patronizing night clubs, or helping relatives and
friends apply for funds.
</P>
<P>
The purpose is prevent corrupt practices by government
officials.
</P>
<P>
The rule also forbids any financial officials from gambling or
playing majiang, going to banquets with government funds from
grass-roots organizations.
</P>
<P>
Department director Huang Gongle said his department will
strengthen enforcement of the rule and welcomes reports of any
violation of it.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has urged other departments to learn
from the Finance Department and take effective measures to build
up clean government.
</P>
<P>
The financial departments, which control the distribution of
large sum of funds, have been called "The God of Wealth" in China.
</P>
<P>
In the past years, some officials in the province took bribes
from grass-roots units, and took money while playing majiang, went
to banquets with government money, and borrowed other units' cars
for personal uses.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
