<HEADLINE> More Farming Machines Used in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The farm machinery market has
been expanding fast with the development of the rural economy in
east China's Jiangsu province in the past several years.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the total power of farm machinery in the province
reached 23 million kw, at about the same level in developed
countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu now has 815,000 tractors, 22,000 havesters and 1.4
million pieces of supporting machinery.
</P>
<P>
Now 55 percent of farm jobs in the province are done by
machines, said local government officials.
</P>
<P>
Increase in grain purchase price and the wider use of advanced
techniques have encouraged the use of farm machinery. And more
farmers are considering buying such machinery for themselves.
</P>
<P>
The craze for farm machinery has brought good profits for
manufacturers. Haima Harvester Plant, the largest farm machinery
manufacturer in the province, completed a business volume of 30
million yuan last year, twice that in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Foreign manufacturers also rushed into the province to get a
share in the market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
