<HEADLINE> Consumer Price Index Rises Slightly in Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The consumer price index climbed
to 106.8 for residents in 35 major cities in January, taking the
prices of the same period of 1996 as 100, according to the latest
statistics released by the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The price index of Beijing stood at 107.1, that of Shanghai
105, and that of Guangzhou 107.5.
</P>
<P>
Shijiazhuang, capital of north China's Hebei Province,
registered the lowest price hike of the month, with its price
index standing at 102.3.
</P>
