<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Nepal's new government, led by
Lokendra Bahadur Chand of the National Democratic Party (RPP),
will bring about political stability and work for all-round
development in the country, a ruling partners' joint statement
said here Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The statement was issued soon after King Birendra appointed RPP
parliamentary leader Chand as prime minister of a new government
which is expected to be joined by the Communist Party of Nepal
(United Marxist Leninist, CPN-UML) and the Nepal Goodwill Party
(NSP).
</P>
<P>
Earlier Monday Chand submitted a petition to the king, claiming
to form the new government with support of a majority of 103 MPs,
including those of the CPN-UML and the NSP, in the 205-seat lower
house.
</P>
<P>
Chand's coalition will replace the outgoing three-party
government led by Sher Bahadur Deuba of the Nepali Congress (NC),
which resigned last Thursday after losing a confidence vote in the
house.
</P>
<P>
The joint statement, issued by Chand, CPN-UML parliamentary
leader Man Mohan Adhikari and NSP leader Gajendra Narayan Singh,
said that the formation of the new government will put an end to
the confusion and uncertainty existing in the country for some
time and help bring about political stability.
</P>
<P>
The main objectives of the government will be to preserve the
independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity of the country
and work for all-round national development, it said.
</P>
<P>
The three leaders promised that the new government will take
institutional and various other practical measures to bring
corruption, financial irregularity and smuggling under control.
</P>
<P>
Pledging that the coalition will work on the basis of national
consensus, the statement called for cooperation from all political
parties to the new government's future measures to be initiated
for the larger interest and prosperity of the country.
</P>
<P>
Within the next few days, the government will come up with
common targets, policies and programs with the objective of
promoting the country's economic development along with social
justice, equality and the well-being of all communities, it said.
 
