<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Procuratorates Deal Harsh Blow to Criminals: Procurator-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- China's procuratorates at all
levels dealt a harsh blow to serious criminal offenses last year,
Procurator-General Zhang Siqing said here today.
</P>
<P>
In his work report of the Supreme People's Procuratorate to the
fifth session of the Eighth National people's Congress (NPC),
Zhang said that the procuratorates nationwide in the past year put
on file for investigation and prosecution a total of 61,099 cases
involving embezzlements, bribes, diversion of public funds and
large amounts of unidentified assets and 21,257 cases in bending
the law for personal gains, fraudulent practices, illegal
custodies, dereliction of duty, violations of citizens' personal
rights and democratic rights, thereby avoiding an otherwise loss
of 6.78 billion yuan for the state and the collective.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that the number of major cases involving Party and
government departments, administrative and law-enforcement
institutions, judicial institutions, and economic management
departments, especially those by leading officials, increased.
</P>
<P>
Of the suspects investigated last year, 13,530 were in the
above-mentioned institutions and departments, up 3.5 percent over
last year. Five of them were officials at the provincial or
ministerial level.
</P>
<P>
A considerable proportion of the cases involved embezzlement
and bribes valued between several hundreds of thousands of yuan
and tens of millions of yuan, with cases involving embezzlement or
bribes valued at more than one million yuan numbering 156 and the
number of cases involving diversion of public funds of over 10
million yuan standing at 57, including five with a value of over
100 million yuan, according to Zhang.
</P>
<P>
As an integral part of the campaign to severely punish
criminals in accordance with the law, the procuratorates approved
arrests of 17 percent more than last year.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that the procuratorates last year approved the
arrests of 18,860 people related to the smuggling, trafficking,
transport and manufacturing of drugs, filing law suits against
18,501 of them.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, procuratorates throughout China contested 2,405
verdicts that were believed to be misjudged or wrongly sentenced
last year, he acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
He added that a great effort was made last year to promote
socialist ethical and cultural progress among the procuratorates.
</P>
<P>
This year China will continue to severely punish criminals
according to law, in order to safeguard national security and
social stability, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, efforts will also be made to fight against
corruption, promote the improvement of the Party's work style and
building of a clean and honest government, strengthen the
supervision of law enforcement, he said, urging procuratorates at
all levels to correctly handle the relations among reform,
development and stability and pay keen attention to the stability
of the social and political environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
