<HEADLINE> NPC Session Holds Fifth Plenum (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
They had also looked into over 21,000 cases of abuse of power
for the benefits of one's friends and relatives, illegal
detention, negligence of duty, and infringement on citizens'
personal and democratic rights, and retrieved a direct economic
loss of 6.78 billion yuan for the state and the collective, he
added.
</P>
<P>
"Generally speaking, the work has been done in a deep-going
way, and certain progress scored," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that last year more than 13,500 criminal suspects,
including staff members of leading Party and government
departments and employees of administrative law-enforcing units,
judicial, and economic administrative departments, were
investigated, up by 3.5 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Among them, 2,699 were leading officials at and above the
county level, including five leaders at the provincial or ministry
level. To date, the procuratorates have ended investigations on
and taken legal proceedings against 961 suspects.
</P>
<P>
The chief procurator said that there are three major tasks for
the procuratorial work this year, which include continuing to wage
the "strike hard" campaign to safeguard national security and
social stability, carrying on the anti-corruption efforts by
probing into major cases to boost the Party morale and build a
clean and honest government, and enhancing supervision over law
enforcement so as to push forward the administration of the
country according to law.
</P>
<P>
"Procuratorates at all levels and their staff must have a clear
understanding of the overall situation, properly handle the
relations between reform, development and stability, pay close
attention to stability in social and political atmosphere, and
insist on the principle of 'enforcing the law seriously and
focusing on handling of cases', to do a good job in various
aspects of the procuratorial work," he demanded.
</P>
<P>
Today's plenum was attended by a total of 2,604 legislators.
</P>
