<HEADLINE> Jiangxi Focus on Construction of Small Hydropower Stations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, March 11 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province
will build more small hydropower stations in rural areas to ease
electricity shortages.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial government says that, the
installed capacity of hydropower stations has reached 900,000 kw,
accounting for 15 percent of the provincial total installed
capacity of power stations.
</P>
<P>
Since 1949, Jiangxi has put in ten billion yuan (about 1.2
billion US dollars) in building 9,800 reservoirs, with a combined
water storage capacity of 15 billion cubic meters. Jiangxi has
4,000 square meters in water resources per capita.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zhengmin, director of the provincial Water Resources
Department says that, Jiangxi will put six billion yuan (714
million US dollars) in hydropower station construction in the next
few years, with a total installed capacity over 200,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2000, the total installed capacity of hydropower
stations in Jiangxi will reach 1.1 million kw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
