<HEADLINE> Alcohol Production in Brazil Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Brazil, the world's
biggest alcohol maker, will produce 1.4 billion liters alcohol
this year, seven percent up from the 1996 output of 1.3 billion
liters.
</P>
<P>
The increase was due to an expected five percent growth in
sugar cane output in the central-south region, an Industry and
Commerce Ministry official said.
</P>
<P>
The bulging alcohol production capacity was expected to bring
about a 1.2 percent expansion in industrial activity, the official
said.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, the biggest sugar cane producer in the world, produced
13 million tons of sugar in the 1996-97 cycle. Sugar cane a major
material for alcohol making. 
</P>
