<DOCNO> XIE19970311.0256 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seventeen Injured in Colombia Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen people,
including two children, were injured today after a bomb exploded
in a cafe in Monteria, northwest Colombia.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said the explosion, which severely damaged
the cafe, happened near the local police station.
</P>
<P>
He described the bomb as a terrorist attack and said it was
related to a bomb explosion last year in the head office of the
Federation of Cattle Ranchers in Cordova in which three people
died.
</P>
<P>
The federation's president was forced to leave the country
after the explosion. The federation supported paramilitary groups
fighting guerrillas in the countryside. 
</P>
</TEXT>
