<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Spares No Effort in Combating Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- China's judicial and
procuratorial systems concentrated their resources last year on
combating serious crimes and, as a result, effectively safeguarded
social stability.
</P>
<P>
Crimes that were dealt with harshly included those that
seriously threatened public security, and embezzlement and
bribery, said Ren Jianxin, president of the Supreme People's
Court, and Zhang Siqing, procurator-general of the Supreme
People's Procuratorate, in their respective work reports to the
ongoing Fifth Session of the Eighth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
To check a rise in crimes in some parts of the country, the
judicial and procuratorial systems, in coordination with pubic
security, state security and administrative departments, launched
what is called a "strike hard" campaign nationwide last April to
crack down on serious crimes.
</P>
<P>
The campaign was aimed at fighting mainly the following crimes:
violent crimes, gun-related crimes, gang crimes, drug-related
crimes, crimes that sabotage the socialist market economic order,
embezzlement, bribery and misappropriation of public fund.
</P>
<P>
The judicial and procuratorial systems also conscientiously
took comprehensive measures to ensure public security and
persisted in combining "strike hard" with "prevention," to
consolidate and develop the achievements of the "strike hard"
campaign.
</P>
<P>
The nationwide campaign has hit hard the arrogance of criminals
and achieved important results as evidenced by a marked
improvement in public order, said Zhang Siqing, the
procurator-general.
</P>
<P>
However, he pointed out, violent crimes, drug-related crimes,
gang crimes and crimes having mafia features still run rampant in
some parts of the country. Consequently, procuratorial
departments will step up the "strike hard" campaign to safeguard
national security and social stability.
</P>
<P>
Ren Jianxin said courts at all levels will steadfastly follow
the principle of harsh and quick punishment in accordance with law
and carry on the campaign, dealing harshly with "criminal
elements" that commit murder, robbery and bombing, and punishing,
in accordance with law, criminals who harm state security.
</P>
<P>
He added the courts will also severely punish those involved in
prostitution, and the production and trading of pornographic
materials and those who organize gambling. Particular attention
will be paid to cracking down on drug-related crimes in accordance
with a national drug elimination plan covering the 1996-2000
period, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
