<HEADLINE> Industrial Investment Rises in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- China's investment by industrial
sectors registered a big increase last year, hitting 690.4 billion
yuan, up 13.8 percent from that of 1995, according to the latest
statistics released by the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that 293.8 billion yuan of investment was
made by the energy sector in 1996, up 21.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Some 150.5 billion yuan of investment was made by the raw
materials sector which includes the businesses of metallurgy,
chemicals, forestry and non-ferrous metals, representing a 2.9
percent increase.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the machinery and electronics industry sector
invested 87.2 billion yuan, and the light and textile industry
sector made a combined investment of 99.9 billion yuan, up 21.1
percent and 10.7 percent, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
