<HEADLINE> Albanian Rebels Agree to Lay Down Arms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Albanian rebels in the key southern
town of Vlore, have agreed to lay down their arms and implement a
peace deal with President Sali Berisha after talks with Italian
diplomats, local media said today.
</P>
<P>
Eight representatives from a rebel committee in the town, at
the forefront of the unrest sweeping the country, signed a
declaration on an Italian warship, the San Giogio, in the Adriatic
Sea after a meeting with the Italian Ambassador to Tirana Paolo
Foresti.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian authorities called on Rome to mediate with the
rebels to try and bring calm to Vlore which has been the scene of
intense fighting between rebels and the Albanian military over the
past 10 days.
</P>
<P>
"The committee ... undertook to favor the immediate handing
back of weapons in the hands of the citizens of Vlore and to
ensure public order and progressively restore normal
administration to the town," the declaration, which was published
by the Italian Foreign Ministry, read.
</P>
<P>
Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini, who paid a whirlwind
visit to Tirana Sunday night, welcomed the statement and pleaded
emergency aid from the international community to help restore
order in the country.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 40 people have died in the violence that has swept
southern Albania in the wake of the collapse of dozens of pyramid
investment schemes in which thousands of people lost their life
savings. They have blamed President Berisha for allowing the
schemes and are demanding his resignation.
</P>
<P>
Berisha was re-elected unopposed by parliament as president for
a second five-year term last week. But on Sunday he was forced to
agree to form an interim coalition government to oversee early
general elections in June, and an grant amnesty to rebels who would
hand in their weapons within a week.
</P>
<P>
Despite Monday's deal with the rebels in Vlore, there were
reports that the revolt was still raging in many southern towns.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
