<HEADLINE> More Overseas-Funded Enterprises for Jinan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 11 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,200 overseas-funded
enterprises have been set up in Jinan, capital of east China's
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of overseas business people and consortia
poured their investment into the four pillar industries of
machinery, automotive, electronics, and chemicals, especially
large, new and hi-tech projects.
</P>
<P>
The city actually utilized more than 200 million US dollars of
overseas funds last year, up 39 percent over the previous
year. Overseas-funded enterprises exported more than 200 million
US dollars of goods, up 33 percent from 1995, according to
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Currently, more than 30 percent of Jinan's overseas-funded
companies are export-oriented.  
</P>
