<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Memorial Hall To Be Built for Pioneering Reformer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The former residence and studio
of a pioneering Chinese reformer in this north China city will be
renovated into a memorial hall.
</P>
<P>
Liang Qichao (1873-1929), a famous scholar and major modern
reformer, moved to the city in 1914. There, he mobilized prominent
general Cai E to fight against Yuan Shikai, who wanted to restore
a dethroned monarch.
</P>
<P>
In 1924, Liang built beside his residence another building
named the "Yinbin Study," where he pursued academic studies and
wrote articles that were later published in "A Collection of the
Yinbin Study."
</P>
<P>
Liang's two buildings, both in Italian-style design, were
listed as relics under city protection in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The renovation work is expected to be completed within three
years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970311.0271 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China City Promotes Science And Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The city of Shantou in south
China's Guangdong Province carried out 99 scientific and
technological projects last year, which are expected to bring an
additional output value of 2.9 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city, one of the four earliest special economic zones in
China, has invested 1.2 billion yuan in the projects.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Shantou scored 50 scientific and technological
achievements, 30 of them reaching national advanced level.
</P>
<P>
The city also held fairs to market the achievements, at which
150 contracts had been signed, involving a transaction value of
120 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In the city's hi-tech development area, an output of 1.72
billion yuan has been realized, while 58 hi-tech products are
waiting to be approved for production.
</P>
<P>
As a result of increasing Sino-overseas scientific and
technological exchange, Shantou exported hi-tech products worth 47
million U.S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that turning scientific and technological
achievements into production has become the major strong point of
the city's economic development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
