<HEADLINE> Investment by Various Sectors Increases Rapidly in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- China's investment by various
economic sectors grew sharply last year, hitting 1,738.8 billion
yuan, up 19.5 percent from that of 1995, according to the latest
statistics released by the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that 33.6 billion yuan of investment was
made by the primary industry, which includes farming, forestry,
animal husbandry, fishery and water conservancy, up 27.5 percent.
