goods, which was expected to be chaired by Indonesia, Santoso
said, adding that ASEAN's import of capital goods was still higher
than its export.
</P>
<P>
The presence of the center was also expected to further enhance
cooperation in trade and investment as well as infrastructure and
tourism sectors among ASEAN countries in accordance with the
ASEAN's Vision Towards the Year 2020, he added.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) groups
Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand
and Vietnam. 
