<HEADLINE> Telecom Business Grows Quickly in Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Chongqing City
registered a fast growth rate in telecommunications last year,
further strengthening its status as a telecom hub for the
landlocked west regions.
</P>
<P>
The latest issue of Communications Weekly said that the city
added 45,000 lines to its local phone switching capacity, raising
the total to 1.04 million lines.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, 15 digital microwave loops with a transmission
speed of 140Mb per second were built in Chongqing's suburbs, and
the long-distance switching system was expanded by 25,000
terminals.
</P>
<P>
So far, the city's GSM (global service of mobile communications)
network, one of the fastest transmission modes for cellular
telephones, has been linked up to other counties.
</P>
<P>
The city's telecom business sustained its growth throughout the
year. About 220,600 rural telephone users, 42,800 mobile phone
clients and 77,000 pager owners were added to the city's telecom
subscription lists. The business revenues of the state-owned
telecom sector increased by 28 percent over the previous year, and
turned out 170 million yuan in profits and taxes.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the city's posts and telecom administration said
that Chongqing will expand the local phone switching capacity by
28 lines this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
