<HEADLINE> China's Investment in Fixed Assests Goes Up in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- China increased its investment in
fixed assets to 2,366 billion yuan in 1996, up 18.2 percent from
the 1995 figure of 2,002 billion yuan, according to the latest
statistics released by the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Among the investment, 839.9 billion yuan was used in capital
construction, up 13.4 percent from 1995.
</P>
<P>
About 374.5 billion yuan was pumped into technical updating and
transformation, an increase of 13.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The real estate projects attracted 382.5 billion yuan, up 21.5
percent. 
