<HEADLINE> Uruguay's Industrial Production Grows in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay's industrial
production increased 3.2 percent in 1996, heralding the start
of a recovery from the recession which began in early 1995.
</P>
<P>
According to the National Institute of Statistics (INE, its
acronym in Spanish), the sector showing the highest growth was
the paper, printing and publishing sector, with an increase of
11.6 percent. Throughout 1996, the food, beverages
and tobacco sectors repeated their good performance in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The INE attributed the growth to investment by industry which
has led to higher productivity by substituting labor for
machinery. INE said the investment had improved Uruguay's
productivity and competitiveness on the local and international
market. 
</P>
