<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan Province
witnessed a swift development in the telecommunications sector
last year, with the telecom business volume reaching 2.05 billion
yuan, or a year-on-year increase of 47.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The lastest issue of Communications Weekly said that in 1996,
the industry experienced the fastest development of recent
decades. The province added 39,600 terminals to its long-distance
telephone network, and expanded its phone switching capacity by
602,000 lines.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Yunnan invested 2.31 billion yuan in the
fixed assets of its telecommunications industry last year, raising
the telephone density rate to 3.16 percent.
</P>
<P>
