<HEADLINE> Spain Qualifies for World Cup Hockey Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Olympic silver medalists
Spain joined South Korea on the road to next year's World Cup,
with a close 2-1 win over South Africa in the qualifying
tournament here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Juan Escarre scored the winning goal in the 68th
minute to help Spain maintain an unbeaten record after four
matches and lead Group A with am unbeatable maximum 12 points.
</P>
<P>
Spain's first goal came from Pablo Usoz from a penalty corner
rebound in the 12th minute, Shaun Cokke equalised through a direct
penalty corner hit in the 29th minute.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand, who missed the last two World Cup finals, staged a
final 10-minute onslaught to defeat Belgium 3-1 in a Group B match
to advance their claim for a semi-final berth.
</P>
<P>
Alexandre De Chaffoy struck first for Belgium after just three
minuites but that was all his side could offer as the humid
conditions took their toll.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand forced Belgium to concede five penalty corners in
the second half, with John Radonovich equalising in the 63rd
minute and then going on to complete a hattrick with goals in the
67th and 69th minutes.
</P>
<P>
The win gave New Zealand 10 points and put them equal second
with Argentina in Group B behind South Korea on 11 points.
</P>
<P>
South Korea play Argentina on Tuesday and a win for the South
Americans would see them grab the top spot and relegate South
Korea to second place.
</P>
<P>
A loss would not hurt South Korea, however, but pave the way
for New Zealand as the top two teams from each group are
guaranteed a place in the finals in Utrecht, the Netherlands in
May next year.
</P>
<P>
A lose to South Korea would mean Argentina would have to
compete in the play-offs between the third and fourth-placed teams
of each group.
</P>
<P>
Belgium completed the preliminary round with seven points to be
in fourth position and head for the classification matches
starting Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Canada who had earlier lost to South Africa and Spain, threw
the second semi-final berth in Group A wide open with a 5-2 win
over Poland.
</P>
<P>
The Canadians are now equal third with Poland on six points,
one behind Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The second semi-finalist will be decided on Tuesday when
Malaysia takes on Spain, Canada play Switzerland and Poland are
against South Africa.
</P>
<P>
At the bottom of Group B, Ireland recorded their first win
Monday by beating Belarus 3-2. Belarus end the tournament with no
points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
