Steels emerging to claim his second success of the year after
winning a stage in the Tour of Majorca.
</P>
<P>
However, his victory was overshadowed by the earlier decision
to bar three cyclists from competing after they failed blood tests
designed to deter use of the drug EPO.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Erwan Mentheour and Italian pair Luca Colombo and
Mauro Santaromita all submitted blood samples which showed red
blood cell levels in excess of the 50 percent limit.
</P>
<P>
EPO, or erythropoietin, a drug produced to treat kidney
disease, is used to increase oxygen-carrying red blood cell levels
which enhance endurance. 
</P>
