<HEADLINE> Indonesian F-16 Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 11 (Xinhua) -- An Indonesian Air Force F-16 jet
crashed at the Halim Perdanakusuma Air Base in east Jakarta
Monday, but there were no immediate reports of casualties.
</P>
<P>
"The plane crashed at 1.30 p.m. (6:30 GMT) in Halim," an
official at the air base said early this morning, but the Air
Force has declined to comment.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Air Force currently has more than 80 combat
aircraft, including 12 F-16s made by the Lockheed Martin Corp. of
the United States. 
</P>
