<HEADLINE> Signori Says No to English Football </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Italian striker Giuseppe Signori
said 'no' to English football, insisting he will stay with Serie A
side Lazio until he retires in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The Lazio skipper, making a brief visit to Milan, said: "I'll
retire in 2000, when I'll be 32, but I want to win the league
championship with Lazio first."
</P>
<P>
Signori has been Serie A's top goalscorer in three of the last
four seasons and was expected to join the exodus of Italian talent
to the English Premiership after being linked with Arsenal,
Chelsea and Newcastle.
</P>
<P>
But he revealed: "I've definitvely dropped the idea of playing
in England.
</P>
<P>
"Our president Sergio Cragnotti has assured me that Lazio will
win something over the next few years and I believe him, " he
said. 
