issued a warning today that cyclone Gavin will hit parts of North
Island Wednesday after playing havoc in Fuji at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The Met Service said winds of up to 110 kmh will hit parts of
Northland, Auckland, Coromandel, Gisborne and some other areas.
</P>
<P>
It also warned that up to 200mm of rain will lash the ranges
and coastal hills around Gisborne and Hawke's Bay in east of the
island.
</P>
<P>
However, it noted that a large high pressure system due to
cross South Island on the same day will stop Gavin from hitting
the entire country.
</P>
<P>
Hawk's Bay grape and process crop growers are hoping that
forecasts would go wrong because the cyclone will put millions of
dollars worth of crops and fruit at risk.
</P>
<P>
Tomato harvesting is only 20 percent completed, most grapes are
still on the vines and apple picking is right in full swing.
