<HEADLINE> New Zealand Wool Export to China Falls Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, March 11 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand's wool export to
China/Hong Kong in the three months to January 1997 dived 50
percent from the same period a year earlier, said Wools of New
Zealand in its latest market review.
</P>
<P>
A total of 12,300 tons of wool were shipped to China/Hong Kong
in the three months, compared with 24,200 tons a year ago, the
review shows.
</P>
<P>
In January, the fall was even sharper with export to China/Hong
Kong slumped 62 percent on a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Despite the drastic fall, China/Hong Kong has remained the
number one customer for New Zealand wool, buying 32 percent of the
country's total export of 186,700 tons in the year ending January.
</P>
