<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 10 (Xinhua) -- France is envisaging establishing a
mini-bridge of humanitarian aid for Rwandan refugees in Ubundu,
eastern Zaire, said the French State Secretary for Emergency
Humanitarian Action Xavier Emmanuelli today.
</P>
<P>
Emmanuelli, who has just paid a visit to Ubundu, said that the
French government has rented a second plane for sending medicines
to Kisangani on Thursday, after a first plane carrying 40 tons of
food and cover sheets arrived in Kisangani today.
</P>
<P>
About 25,000 to 30,000 Hutu refugees have fled their camp in
Ubundu after the rebels took the city from government troops.
</P>
<P>
Although the refugees are not suffering from severe
mal-nutrition now, their food will run out in three days, said
French officials.
</P>
<P>
French officials also described as "preoccupying" the
situation of about 3,500 refugees, including 150 children, who are
living in an abandoned hospital in Kisangani. 
</P>
