<HEADLINE> Dow Sets New Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Strength in high tech, drug and
energy issues helped lift the New York stock market higher and
pushed the Dow Jones industry average to a new height today.
</P>
<P>
The main gauge of blue chips gained 78.50 points to close at
7,079.39, a new all-time high, beating the previous record of
7,067.46 set on Feb. 18.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners on the New York Stock
Exchange by a margin of nearly 2-to-1. Volume was 458.75 million,
down from 505.84 million on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Also advancing to a record high was the NYSE composite index,
which rose rose 3.87 to 427.70, marginally besting the Feb. 18
record of 427.07.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock index gained 8.68 to 813.65.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 10.92 to 1,322.72 and the
American Stock Exchange Market Value Index rose 1.57 to 603.63.
</P>
<P>
There was little economic data released today, allowing
investors to focus in on different sectors that have been weak
lately and snapped up some bargains.
</P>
<P>
Oil refiners and equipment makers also rallied.
</P>
<P>
A key inflation indicator will be released later in the week
with a government report on producer prices.  
</P>
