<HEADLINE> S. African Mining Output, Sales Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 11 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's mining
production for the fourth quarter of last year increased by one
percent after seasonal adjustment compared with the third
quarter, central statistical services in Pretoria said.
</P>
<P>
The value of mineral sales increased by 10 percent after
seasonal adjustment during the same period, said the services.
</P>
<P>
Total mining production increased by one percent. This was
attributed to a 2.2 percent increase in gold production, the
services noted.
</P>
<P>
Significant increases were also recorded in non-gold
production with chrome up 12.2 percent and diamonds up 6.3
percent, while the sales of coal and manganese increased by 6.7
percent and 15 percent respectively, the services said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
